<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-587-619  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 587 619.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Nov 5 1990 v24 n44 p105(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Technical hurdles remain: language confusion and escalatingcomplexities. (imaging systems) (Image Processing Systems SpecialReport)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Menta, Terry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The development of imaging systems can be accelerated ifinterested parties clarify the terminology describing this youngindustry and examine the various application groups relevant toit.andP;  'Document image processing' is the descriptor of choice forthis field, since 'document' can refer to items ranging fromchecks to large sketches and 'processing' emphasizes the issue ofmobility.andP;  Document image processing has entered the market mainlyas a means of document storage and retrieval, but it is alsowell-suited to work flow applications that could save time byconverting all incoming documents into images as they arrive at abusiness location.andP;  Other key application areas include those ofimage-aided data entry, item processing and knowledge-workeraugmentation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Imaging TechnologyImage processingTerminologyComputer industryDocument ProcessingApplicationsProduct Development.andO;Feature:   illustrationcartoon.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>